# Vercel Deployment Instructions

## Step 1: Deploy to Vercel

1. **Connect GitHub Repository:**
   - Go to https://vercel.com
   - Sign in and click "New Project"
   - Connect your GitHub account
   - Select the "zendesk-alternative" repository

2. **Configure Deployment:**
   - Framework: React (Vite)
   - Root Directory: . (leave default)
   - Build Command: npm run build
   - Output Directory: dist

3. **Deploy:**
   - Click "Deploy"
   - Vercel will automatically build and deploy your app

## Step 2: Database Setup (JSONBin.io)

1. **Create Free JSONBin Account:**
   - Go to https://jsonbin.io
   - Sign up for free account
   - Create a new bin
   - Copy the Bin ID and API Key

2. **Update API Functions:**
   - Replace JSONBIN_URL in `api/emails.js` and `api/stats.js`
   - Replace JSONBIN_KEY with your actual API key

## Step 3: Test Production

1. **Frontend:** https://your-app-name.vercel.app
2. **API Health:** https://your-app-name.vercel.app/api/health  
3. **Admin Page:** https://your-app-name.vercel.app/admin

## Alternative Database Options

### Option 1: Railway PostgreSQL
- More robust for high traffic
- Better for production apps

### Option 2: Supabase
- PostgreSQL with built-in admin UI
- Real-time features

### Option 3: Firebase Firestore
- NoSQL database
- Real-time updates

## Production Features

✅ **Working:**
- Email collection from any device
- Real-time admin dashboard  
- CSV export functionality
- Cross-device compatibility
- CORS properly configured

✅ **Scalable:**
- Serverless functions auto-scale
- Database handles concurrent requests
- No server maintenance required
